HEADWORD: Ailette
<hw>Ai*lette</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>ailette</ets>, dim. of <ets>aile</ets> wing, L.
<ets>ala</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small square shield, formerly worn on the
shoulders of knights, -- being the prototype of the modern
epaulet.</def> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

